implicit type constitutive relations are adequate for fitting the one dimensional (shear stress versus shear
rate) experimental data, and we speculate about the possible form of the corresponding three
dimensional (Cauchy stress tensor versus symmetric part of the velocity gradient) implicit constitutive
relations. Using the representation theorem for isotropic tensorial functions we conjecture that the
implicit constitutive relations could lead to novel models capable to describe nonzero normal stress differences.
