2.54, 4.45 and 7 mm. Also, the effect of the cuttings shape with 1, 0.9 and 0.85 was investigated and it
was found that higher sphereicity have better cleaning efficiency. Conclusion: The analyses revealed
that for 30° diverted orientation; the effective cleaning performance was achieved when the drilling
mud charging was higher than 800 GPM for all types of tested cuttings. The simulation results
revealed that there was a significant effect of the cuttings size on the cuttings transport. Fine particles
are the easiest to clean out.},
