tails about slug flow in vertical pipes. The knowledge gained from this work can be used to reestablish existing empirical correlations that are limited to particular conditions but necessary to the mechanistic models. The improvement of mechanistic models can benefit the design of tubing and surface facilities and the determination of artificial-lift methods.},
