bubble columns and bubbly pipe flows, stirred tanks, cyclones, and a fluid catalytic
cracking unit. The fluid catalytic cracking unit is used to illustrate the complexity of
the physical phenomena involved, and the possibilities and limitations of the different
approaches used: Eulerian–Lagrangian (particle-tracking) and Eulerian–Eulerian
