le set of drilling parameters.Annular pressure losses depend on fluid rheology, flow regime and the geometry of the annulus, Previous models treat either concentric or eccentric annuli and assume uniformity along the wellbore.Concentric annular flow has received considerable attention, At laminar flow conditions exact models are available for Newtonian, power law and Bingham plastic fluids, Recently, Reed and Pilehvari proposed a model for laminar, transitional and turbulent flows. This model extends well established results on Newtonian and non-Newtonian pipe flow-in particular Dodge and Metzner's work to concentric annular flow.Models also exist for uniformly eccentric annuli in laminar flow, analytical for Newtonian and numerical for non-Newtonian fluids.P. 113\^},
