  abstract = {The independent analysis of flow measurements is frequently hampered by incomplete characterisation of the
working fluid. This problem is particularly acute in situations which require working fluids with identical properties,
such as the development of scaling laws for the turbulent flow of drag-reducing liquids. In this paper, we demonstrate
that the viscometric viscosity, loss and storage moduli for two of the most common polymers used for flow
