given concentration in water, the properties of certain non-Newtonian liquids, such as CMC and XG, are essentially
fixed and reproducible. Although the situation is less than ideal, comparisons of fluid-flow data from entirely independent
laboratories can thus be made even in the absence of direct rheological measurements.},
